---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy - Pikos" description="Pikos privacy policy. Your data stays on your device. Plain language, no legalese.">

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-8 py-20">

    <!-- Back to home -->
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-neutral-400 transition-colors hover:text-primary-500 dark:text-neutral-500 dark:hover:text-primary-400">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
      Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-8 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-400 dark:text-neutral-500">Effective: May 17, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">

      <p>
        This policy is short because there isn't much to say.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Your data stays on your device</h2>

      <p>
        Everything you create in Pikos (notes, tasks, calendar events, folders, and settings) is stored in a standard, open database format on your machine. There is no sign-up and no way for us to see what you write. You can copy, back up, or move your data at any time; there is no lock-in.
      </p>

      <p>
        We cannot access, read, or recover your data. If you delete the app, the data goes with it unless you've backed it up yourself.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Network connections</h2>

      <p>
        The app's only built-in network request is an update check when you launch it. Nothing about you or your data is sent, and you can turn it off in Settings → General.
      </p>

      <p>
        Any future feature that needs the network will be opt-in, a toggle in Settings. If you turn one on, the relevant third-party provider's privacy policy governs whatever data flows through them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Website analytics</h2>

      <p>
        This website uses privacy-focused analytics to count page views and downloads. No cookies, no fingerprinting, no cross-site tracking. We see aggregate numbers: how many people visit each page and download the app. We cannot identify individual visitors.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Changes to this policy</h2>

      <p>
        If this policy changes, we'll update the date at the top. For material changes, like collecting new data, we'll note it clearly here and in the app.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-50">Contact</h2>

      <p>
        Questions about privacy? Email <a href="mailto:hello@pikos.app" class="text-primary-500 hover:underline">hello@pikos.app</a>.
      </p>

    </div>

  </main>

  <Footer current="/privacy" />
</Base>

<style>

  </style>
